answer: There is no clear correlation between the acquisition year and the licensed operational duration. The durations are: Pilgrim (acquired 1999) - 60 years, FitzPatrick (2000) - 59 years, Indian Point 3 (2000) - 39 years, Indian Point 2 (2001) - 39 years, Vermont Yankee (2002) - 60 years, and Palisades (2007) - 60 years. Plants acquired more recently (e.g., Palisades in 2007) have long durations (60 years), while some acquired earlier (e.g., Indian Point plants in 2000/2001) have much shorter durations (39 years). The duration seems to be independent of the acquisition date.
